22/05/2003
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The European Commission (EC) approved on Wednesday (21 May) a communication to the Council and the European Parliament on the Western Balkans and European integration. 
The document proposes polices aiming to reinforce EU enlargement in the region. 
The EC plans to introduce European Integration Partnerships to enhance institution building through twinning programmes, technical assistance and increased participation in community programmes. 
(HINA, EU website - 21/05/03)
